==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elutriate
<hw>E*lu"tri*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Elutriated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Elutriating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>elutriatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>elutriare</ets>.]</ety> <def>To
wash or strain out so as to purify; <as>as, to <ex>elutriate</ex> the
blood as it passes through the lungs</as>; to strain off or decant, as a
powder which is separated from heavier particles by being drawn off with
water; to cleanse, as by washing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elutriation</ent>⟦br⟧
